China Journalist’s Death Not ‘Gutter Oil’ Related, Business News Reports

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-09-22T00:18:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-22/china-journalist-s-death-not-gutter-oil-related-business-news-reports.html
The death of a journalist in
central  China  was not related to his previous reporting about
the “gutter oil,” the China Business News reported today,
citing the Luoyang Municipal Public Security Bureau.  Li Xiang, a journalist working for Luoyang Television, was
robbed and stabbed to death in the early morning of Sept. 18,
the report said, citing Li Hongjiang, a deputy head of the
public security bureau. “Gutter oil” is reprocessed waste oil
taken from restaurants.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bloomberg News at 
 jliu42@bloomberg.net  